102175.name: Aftershocks
102175.text: Deal 1 damage to all minions, three times. Costs (2) less if you cast a spell last turn.

102061.name: Amphibious Elixir
102061.flavorText: Made by frogs, for frogs, from frogs.

100938.name: Antique Flinger
100938.text: Battlecry: If you've Excavated twice, destroy an enemy minion.
100938.flavorText: One man's treasure is another man's statue to the face.

101093.name: Azerite Chain Gang
101093.text: Taunt Battlecry and Quickdraw: Summon a copy of this.
101093.flavorText: How long can this go on? For 6 years at least!

100234.name: Azerite Giant
100234.text: Costs (1) less for each turn in a row you've played an Elemental.
100234.flavorText: Either that giant isn't really giant, or that doorway is HUGE!

101849.name: Azerite Vein
101849.text: Secret: When the enemy plays a card on the turn that it entered their hand, get a copy that costs (0).
101849.flavorText: When the ground trembles near it, are those earthquakes or heartbeats?

100546.name: Badlands Brawler
100546.text: Battlecry: Start a Brawl! If you've Excavated twice, this always wins.
100546.flavorText: Watch out watch out watch out - R.K.O. outta nowhere!

100367.name: Bartend-O-Bot
100367.text: Battlecry: Draw an Outcast card and slide it to the left side of your hand.
100367.flavorText: Bartend-O-Bot! Make my Outcast card DO SOMETHING!

100539.name: Battlepickaxe
100539.text: After you play a Taunt minion, gain +1 Durability.
100539.flavorText: You can pick your battles, and you can pick your axes, but you can't uh… pick your friends' battlepickaxes?

101955.name: Benevolent Banker
101955.text: Battlecry: Discover a spell from your deck. Quickdraw: Enemy deck instead.
101955.flavorText: "Oh no, you've got me confused. I'm Ben, the evil ent banker. I only work with evil trees!"

101480.name: Blast Charge
101480.text: Destroy a damaged enemy minion. Excavate a treasure.

100537.name: Blast Tortoise
100537.text: Taunt Battlecry: Deal damage to all enemy minions equal to this minion's Attack.
100537.flavorText: Who's that minion? ... Iiiiit's Blast Tortoise! "Blast tortoise."

101875.name: Blastmage Miner
101875.text: Battlecry: Excavate a treasure. For each card in your hand, deal 1 damage to a random enemy.

100358.name: Blindeye Sharpshooter
100358.text: After you play a Naga, deal 2 damage to a random enemy and draw a spell. (Then switch!) After you cast a spell, deal 2 damage to a random enemy and draw a Naga. (Then switch!)

101367.name: Boomboss Tho'grun
101367.text: Battlecry: Shuffle 3 T.N.T. into your opponent's deck. When drawn, blow up a card in their hand, deck, and board.
101367.flavorText: Ever since the Bloodrock Company hired this guy, business has been booming!

98769.name: Bounty Board
98769.text: Your Excavate, Quickdraw, Tradeable, and Legendary cards cost (1) less.
98769.flavorText: Reno's desire to be a face known around the Badlands might have backfired a little bit.

101133.name: Bounty Wrangler
101133.flavorText: With a smile like that and Coins in her hands, she's one greedy grinner.

100173.name: Bovine Skeleton
100173.text: Deathrattle: If this has 4 or more Attack, summon a Bovine Skeleton.
100173.flavorText: The secret cow level has been unearthed.

101971.name: Bunny Stomper
101971.flavorText: Has a PhD in stomputational chemistry.

102249.name: Burning Heart
102249.text: Deal 2 damage to a minion. If it survives, give your hero +3 Attack this turn.
102249.flavorText: A 100% ethically sourced fire elemental heart is very hard to come by. This one definitely wasn't.

98768.name: Burrow Buster
98768.flavorText: We almost went with the name "Giant Drill", but then it would've HAD to be an 8/8.

101976.name: Cactus Construct
101976.text: Discover a 2-Cost minion. Summon a 1/2 copy of it.
101976.flavorText: "I am not Malfurion! I am CACTUS LORD!"

100019.name: Cactus Cutter
100019.text: Battlecry: Draw a spell. If you cast it this turn, gain +1/+2 and Taunt.

101461.name: Cactus Rager
101461.flavorText: What doesn't kill ya makes you deader.

100174.name: Camouflage Mount
100174.text: Give a minion +3/+3 and a random Bonus Effect. When it dies, summon a Chameleon.
100174.flavorText: What mount? I don't see anything…

100553.name: Cattle Rustler
100553.text: Battlecry: Draw a Beast. It costs (3) less.
100553.flavorText: What once started as a small-time cat burglary gig has turned into a life of cattle rustling. What a shame.

102443.name: Chaos Creation
102443.text: Deal 6 damage. Summon a random 6-Cost minion. Destroy the bottom 6 cards of your deck.
102443.flavorText: So THIS is who's been Greening everything!

101376.name: Corpse Farm
101376.text: Spend up to 8 Corpses to summon a random minion of that Cost.
101376.flavorText: It ain't much, but it's dishonest work.

104530.name: Crimson Expanse
104530.text: Choose a damaged minion. Summon a copy of it that goes Dormant for one turn.

101265.name: Crop Rotation
101265.text: Summon four 1/1 Undead with Rush that die at the end of turn.
101265.flavorText: "Dave, you're never gunna believe this! The plants ARE the zombies!"

99221.name: Cryopreservation
99221.flavorText: Remember to take the elementals out of the freezer before Mom gets home!

102432.name: Crystal Cluster
102432.text: Gain three empty Mana Crystals. Any that can't fit summon a 3/7 Elemental with Taunt.
102432.flavorText: And if you can't fit any of the Elementals… do better.

102129.name: Dang-Blasted Elemental
102129.text: Taunt Deathrattle: Deal 2 damage to all minions except friendly Elementals.
102129.flavorText: We were told that "Dag-Nabbin' Dang-Blastin' Rootin'-Tootin' High-Falutin' Elemental" was too long.

99129.name: Dart Throw
99129.text: Throw two 2 damage darts at random enemy minions. (If both hit the same minion, get a Coin!)
99129.flavorText: Did you know: Hitting the same target twice is only for skilled players. This has been a 'Dart Fact'!

104528.name: Deepminer Brann
104528.text: Battlecry: If your deck started with no duplicates, your Battlecries trigger twice for the rest of the game.
104528.flavorText: This is a very on-brannd effect.

100015.name: Dehydrate
100015.text: Lifesteal. Deal 4 damage to a minion. Quickdraw: Costs (1).
100015.flavorText: JUST A LITTLE FURTHER LITTLE GUY, YOU CAN MAKE IT!!!

100195.name: Deputization Aura
100195.text: Your left-most minion has +1 Attack and Lifesteal. Lasts turns.
100195.flavorText: You're my favorite deput- oh. You died… Ok just kidding, THAT guy is my favorite deputy.

101978.name: Desert Nestmatron
101978.text: Taunt. Battlecry: If you're holding a Dragon, refresh 4 Mana Crystals.
101978.flavorText: Not as sweet as the Dessert Nestmatron, but still just as refreshing!

100062.name: Detonation Juggernaut
100062.flavorText: Did you really need a whole giant mecha-suit just for one bundle of dynamite?

102173.name: Digging Straight Down
102173.text: Deal 8 damage to a minion. Excavate a treasure.
102173.flavorText: You only make this mistake once.

101269.name: Disposal Assistant
101269.text: Battlecry and Deathrattle: Put a Barrel of Sludge on the bottom of your deck.
101269.flavorText: A bright green liquid that people say is bad for you... That's either hazardous waste OR a new popular brand of soft drink.

99961.name: Doctor Holli'dae
99961.text: Battlecry: If your deck started with no duplicates, equip the Staff of the Nine Frogs.
99961.flavorText: If anything can heal the Badlands, it is the power of frogs!

101053.name: Dragon Golem
101053.text: Taunt Battlecry: Summon a copy of this for each Dragon in your hand.
101053.flavorText: I have a Dragon, I have a Golem. UH! Dragon Golem!

101369.name: Dragon Tales
101369.text: Choose One - Get two random Dragons that cost (5) or less; or Get two that cost more than (5).
101369.flavorText: "Once upon a time, there was a maaaagical toy shop, filled with wonder and Dragons!"

100944.name: Drilly the Kid
100944.flavorText: "I HATE that nickname. Call me Drilliam!"

101483.name: Dryscale Deputy
101483.text: Battlecry: The next time you draw a spell, get a copy of it.
101483.flavorText: He's here to tip the scales in our favor… and moisturize them too.

102435.name: Elementium Geode
102435.text: Battlecry and Deathrattle: Draw a card. Deal 2 damage to your hero.

101989.name: Elise, Badlands Savior
101989.text: Battlecry: If your deck started with no duplicates, summon 5/5 copies of 4 random minions in your deck.
101989.flavorText: From the library to the field, she's proved herself to be a leading intellectual.

101877.name: Eroded Sediment
101877.text: Battlecry: If you played an Elemental last turn, Discover any Elemental from the past.
101877.flavorText: A perfect minion for those feeling sedimental about their past.

100362.name: Fan the Hammer
100362.text: Deal 6 damage split among the lowest Health enemies.
100362.flavorText: I thought Kurtrus was more of a fan of glaives.

100627.name: Farm Hand
100627.flavorText: I know it's an Undead hand, but bending your pinky in that way can NOT be good for your joints.

102252.name: Fel Fissure
102252.text: Deal 2 damage to all minions. At the start of your next turn, deal 2 more damage to all minions.
102252.flavorText: This will clear the board, I'm fisSURE of it!

100611.name: Fistful of Corpses
100611.text: Deal damage to a minion equal to your Corpses.

101476.name: Flint Firearm
101476.text: Battlecry: Get a random Quickdraw card. If you play it this turn, repeat this.
101476.flavorText: You'll never guess why they call him that.

102421.name: Fool's Gold
102421.text: Get a random Golden Pirate and Elemental from other classes.

102728.name: Fossilized Kaleidosaur
102728.text: Battlecry: Gain two random Bonus Effects. Excavate a treasure.
102728.flavorText: He's not that bad if you don't die turn 4.

102148.name: Fracking
102148.text: Look at the bottom 3 cards of your deck. Draw one and destroy the others.
102148.flavorText: For fhe person who jusf cannof decide whaf card fo puf info a deck!

102903.name: Furnace Fuel
102903.text: When this is played, discarded, or destroyed, draw 2 cards.
102903.flavorText: Remember Ultrasaur? This is him now. Feel old yet?

101057.name: Fye, the Setting Sun
101057.text: Rush, Lifesteal, Taunt Costs (1) less for each Dragon you've summoned this game.
101057.flavorText: There is a dragon way down in Bloodrock They call the Setting Sun

102170.name: Gaslight Gatekeeper
102170.text: Battlecry: Shuffle your hand into your deck, then draw that many cards.
102170.flavorText: This girl is such a boss.

101881.name: Gattlesnake
101881.text: At the end of your turn, load two bullets that deal 1 damage each. Deathrattle: Fire at random enemies!
101881.flavorText: He used to be an ordinary snake until he slithered through a saloon during a brawl and walked out looking like this.

102059.name: Giant Tumbleweed!!!
102059.text: Deal 6 damage to all minions. Summon a 6/6 Tumbleweed.
102059.flavorText: Skarr's second-biggest hobby after laying waste to the Badlands is bowling.

102427.name: Gloomstone Guardian
102427.text: Taunt. Choose One - Discard 2 cards; or Destroy one of your Mana Crystals. Forge: Do NEITHER.
102427.flavorText: From the same people who brought you Choose One, and Choose Twice, comes the exciting prequel: Choose NEITHER!

102424.name: Glowstone Gyreworm
102424.flavorText: Believe it or not, this is Tram Conductor Gerry's Gyreworm. But is it pronounced Gerry's Gyreworm, Gerry's Gyreworm, Gerry's Gyreworm, or Gerry's Gyreworm?

101966.name: Gold Panner
101966.text: At the end of your turn, draw a card.
101966.flavorText: "I don't know why everyone's got their overalls in a jumble with Azerite minin' when there's all this GOLD for the takin'!"

98704.name: Greedy Partner
98704.text: Battlecry: If you're holding another 2-Cost card, get a Coin.
98704.flavorText: "Don't worry, we'll evenly split the bounty. Then I'll have two evenly sized piles of gold!"

98652.name: Gunslinger Kurtrus
98652.text: Battlecry: If your deck started with no duplicates, fire six 2 damage shots at minions in the enemy's hand.
98652.flavorText: "I have given up (a single copy of) EVERYTHING! What have YOU sacrificed?"

100616.name: Harrowing Ox
100616.text: Taunt Battlecry: If you've Excavated twice, your next card this turn costs (7) less.
100616.flavorText: Dead or alive, you're pulling that plow.

101462.name: Heat Wave
101462.text: Deal 2 damage to an enemy minion and its neighbors. Quickdraw: To all enemies instead.
101462.flavorText: This is the hottest summer of your life so far.

100284.name: Hi Ho Silverwing
100284.flavorText: I swear this minion had 3000 Attack at one point!

102422.name: Hidden Gem
102422.text: Stealth At the end of your turn, restore 2 Health to all friendly characters.
102422.flavorText: This will be a staple in Unicorn Priest.

102171.name: High Noon Duelist
102171.text: Deathrattle: Both players DRAW! Destroy the card that costs less.
102171.flavorText: "My ultimate is rea- ah, errr, I mean, I have enough Mana."

100118.name: Holy Cowboy
100118.text: Battlecry: Your next Holy spell costs (2) less.
100118.flavorText: Wait, but… Isn't he more of a 'holy kodoboy'?

102054.name: Holy Springwater
102054.text: Restore 8 Health to a damaged character. Save any excess in a 1-Cost Bottle.
102054.flavorText: Issa bah oh auh woh ah!

98701.name: Horseshoe Slinger
98701.text: Battlecry: Deal 2 damage to a random enemy minion. Quickdraw: And one of its neighbors.
98701.flavorText: Some people think this card is broken, but I think it's farrier than that.

100113.name: Howdyfin
100113.text: Whenever your hand has less than 3 cards in it, get a random Murloc.
100113.flavorText: You know who to blame if your drinking water tastes a little fishy.

101481.name: Injured Hauler
101481.text: Battlecry: Deal 4 damage to this minion. Overheal: Deal 2 damage to all enemy minions.
101481.flavorText: With how many cacti are all over the Badlands, this job has to be some sort of sick joke.

102051.name: Invasive Shadeleaf
102051.text: Deal 10 damage to an enemy minion. Save any excess in a 1-Cost Bottle.

102733.name: Iridescent Gyreworm
102733.text: Deathrattle: Give each of your minions a random Bonus Effect.

101555.name: Kingpin Pud
101555.flavorText: The good, the bad, and the ugly stats for the Cost.

98762.name: Kobold Miner
98762.flavorText: A mining kobold that costs 2, has very low health, and gives you resources… what is this, Warcraft Rumble?

100230.name: Lawful Longarm
100230.text: Rush, Lifesteal Battlecry: Gain +1 Attack for each card in your hand.
100230.flavorText: Loves to lob law bombs from his law blog.

101142.name: Lay Down the Law
101142.text: Tradeable Set a minion's Attack and Health to 1. Quickdraw: Then deal 1 damage to it.
101142.flavorText: The official term for "Because I said so!".

101968.name: Linedance Partner
101968.text: Battlecry: If you're holding another 3-Cost card, summon a random 3-Cost minion.
101968.flavorText: Where did you come from? (Linedance Partner's Battlecry) Where did you go? (Face)

101162.name: Living Horizon
101162.text: Taunt, Divine Shield Costs (1) less for each other card in your hand.
101162.flavorText: Even in the darkest of days, the sun never sets on the Badlands.

100286.name: Living Prairie
100286.text: Battlecry: If you played an Elemental last turn, summon two 3/3 Cows with Rush.
100286.flavorText: Whoooooa, we're half way there Whooa-oh, -

100369.name: Load the Chamber
100369.text: Deal 2 damage. Your next Naga, Fel spell, and weapon cost (1) less.
100369.flavorText: Wait! Before we duel, I gotta install these shaders.

102160.name: Mantle Shaper
102160.text: Costs (1) less for each spell you've cast while holding this.
102160.flavorText: You got a fireplace? I've got a guy who shapes mantles.

102741.name: Maruut Stonebinder
102741.text: Battlecry: If your deck started with no duplicates, Discover an Elemental to summon. Add the others to your hand.
102741.flavorText: Savior of the World Pillar, Maruut valiantly fought the Twilight's Hammer to aid Therazane against the Cataclysm.

100619.name: Maw and Paw
100619.text: At the end of your turn, gain 5 Corpses. At the start of your turn, spend 5 Corpses to give your hero +5 Health.
100619.flavorText: Home is where the disfigured, rotten heart is.

101879.name: Mes'Adune the Fractured
101879.text: Battlecry: Draw an Elemental. Split it into two halves.
101879.flavorText: Cracking open an elemental with the boys.

100191.name: Messenger Buzzard
100191.text: Deathrattle: Draw a Beast. Give minions in your hand +1/+1.
100191.flavorText: The bird brings the word (which happens to be bird).

100363.name: Midnight Wolf
100363.flavorText: Three of these would make for an EPIC T-shirt.

100016.name: Minecart Cruiser
100016.text: Rush, Overload: (2) Battlecry: If you played an Elemental last turn, don't Overload.
100016.flavorText: Where are you drivin', Minecart Cruiser? Where is your bounty, fortune, and fame?

102418.name: Mining Casualties
102418.text: Summon two 1/1 Silver Hand Recruits with "Deathrattle: Summon a 1/1 Frail Ghoul".

100101.name: Miracle Salesman
100101.flavorText: "Hey! Hope you’re well. Have you ever wanted to be your own boss?"

100540.name: Misfire
100540.text: Deal 3, 2, and 1 damage to random minions. Quickdraw: Choose the targets.

102151.name: Mismatched Fossils
102151.text: Discover a Beast and an Undead. Swap their stats.
102151.flavorText: Whoever put these fossils together must be really careless.

102904.name: Mo'arg Drillfist
102904.flavorText: Also functions as the town dentist.

102172.name: Needlerock Totem
102172.text: At the end of your turn, gain 2 Armor and draw a card.
102172.flavorText: You put the Needlerock in to get the Bloodrock out.

100361.name: Oasis Outlaws
100361.text: Discover a Naga. If you've played a Naga while holding this, reduce its Cost by (1).
100361.flavorText: With their oasis polluted by the Bloodrock Mining Company, Snake Eyes has set aside her differences with the outlaws of the Badlands to put an end to Bloodrock's operation.

102161.name: Obsidian Revenant
102161.text: Taunt Deathrattle: Summon two random Deathrattle minions that cost (3) or less.
102161.flavorText: What is this? A Reven for Ants?!

101551.name: Ogre-Gang Ace
101551.text: Rush Whenever this attacks, gain Divine Shield. (50% chance to gain Lifesteal instead.)
101551.flavorText: 100% chance to not play by the rules.

101549.name: Ogre-Gang Outlaw
101549.text: Rush 50% chance to attack the wrong enemy.
101549.flavorText: Why don't they just buy another hat?

101550.name: Ogre-Gang Rider
101550.text: Rush 50% chance to give your hero +3 Attack this turn instead of attacking.
101550.flavorText: Doesn't know his ride from his left.

101873.name: Overflow Surger
101873.text: Battlecry: Summon a copy of this for each turn in a row you've played an Elemental. ( )
101873.flavorText: The drip on this elemental is straight fire!

100365.name: Parched Desperado
100365.text: Battlecry: If you've cast a spell while holding this, give your hero +3 Attack this turn.
100365.flavorText: I'm green And I'm about to die Da ba dee da ba di

102426.name: Pendant of Earth
102426.text: Discover a minion from your deck. Restore Health to your hero equal to its Cost.

99959.name: Pile of Bones
99959.text: Deathrattle: The next time you Excavate, resummon this.
99959.flavorText: It's a very well-organized pile, I'll give you that.

102052.name: Pip the Potent
102052.text: Battlecry: Copy each 1-Cost card in your hand.
102052.flavorText: One time, I was trying to get Pip's attention to warn her that the dangerous outlaw Cheery Ollie, who also goes by just 'O', was headed her way. "Pip! Pip! Cheery O!", I shouted.

100359.name: Pocket Sand
100359.text: Deal 3 damage. Quickdraw: Your opponent's next card costs (1) more.
100359.flavorText: I was only trying to get it in your eyes, man. YOU didn't need to open your mouth like that!

102144.name: Pop'gar the Putrid
102144.text: Your Fel spells cost (2) less and have Lifesteal. Battlecry: Get two Barrels of Sludge.
102144.flavorText: All around the arid badlands The Outlaws chased the Townsfolk Gerry had a train full of sludge POP! goes the sludge train

104999.name: Posse Possession
104999.text: Summon a 4/4 copy of a random minion in your opponent's hand.
104999.flavorText: Keep your friends close, your enemies closer, and your shadows at gunpoint.

100121.name: Prismatic Beam
100121.text: Deal 3 damage to all enemies. Costs (1) less for each enemy minion.
100121.flavorText: Seven colors of the rainbow, one for each enemy minion.

104524.name: Prosthetic Hand
104524.flavorText: It's creaky and it's rusty! It's spooky and it's dusty!

104523.name: Quartzite Crusher
104523.text: Lifesteal. Freeze any character damaged by your hero.
104523.flavorText: It's not just a weapon… it's a rock!

102254.name: Quick Pick
102254.text: After your hero attacks, draw a card.
102254.flavorText: QUICK! Pick which quick pick trick will stick in the thick of the wick! Lickety split!

100595.name: Reap What You Sow
100595.flavorText: With a hat like that, I'd say their tailor did all of the sowing.

101054.name: Rehydrate
101054.flavorText: Just doing our part as the Hearthstone development team in reminding you to drink more water!

100114.name: Reinforced Plating
100114.flavorText: I am become death, destroyer of azerite.

101939.name: Reliquary Researcher
101939.text: Battlecry: If you've Excavated twice, cast two random Mage Secrets.
101939.flavorText: What good is a researcher if they're just gunna keep it all a secret?

103471.name: Reno, Lone Ranger
103471.text: Battlecry: If your deck started with no duplicates, remove all enemy minions from the game.
103471.flavorText: With an uncertain past and a questionable future, Reno was lucky to find his home on the range.

101375.name: Reska, the Pit Boss
101375.text: Rush. Costs (1) less for each minion that died this game. Deathrattle: Take control of a random enemy minion.
101375.flavorText: Overseer of the Bloodrock Mine, Reska will work you to the bone. They'll then reanimate your bones and work THOSE bones to the bone.

101055.name: Rheastrasza
101055.text: Battlecry: If your deck started with no duplicates, summon the Purified Dragon Nest.
101055.flavorText: Rheastrasza ascends above loyalty to just her dragonflight to serve all dragonkind. She believes all flights deserve a future and will give her life for the future dragon prince.

98750.name: Rowdy Partner
98750.text: Battlecry: If you're holding another 4-Cost card, deal 4 damage.

100178.name: Saddle Up!
100178.text: Give your minions "Deathrattle: Summon a random Beast that costs (3) or less."
100178.flavorText: And then they rode off into the sunset, not knowing they left their stove on.

101871.name: Saloon Brewmaster
101871.text: Battlecry: Return a friendly minion to your hand. Give it +2/+2.
101871.flavorText: Brewmaster Bru brought Barrelbrim bursting barrels of barely brewed barley brew. Barrelbrim bought Bru's barley brew, barring the barrels broken from the brazen brunch brawl.

102250.name: Shadestone Skulker
102250.text: Rush. Battlecry: Take your weapon and gain its stats. Deathrattle: Give it back.
102250.flavorText: Sharing is caring - and they don't care.

104537.name: Shadow Word: Steal
104537.text: Return an enemy minion to YOUR hand.
104537.flavorText: Anduin will literally take your stuff and say it's a Shadow Word.

102732.name: Shale Spider
102732.text: Battlecry: If you played an Elemental last turn, draw a card.
102732.flavorText: The 2nd member of the VERY exclusive Is-Called-A-Spider-But-Isn't-A-Beast Club.

102423.name: Shattered Reflections
102423.text: Choose a minion. Add a copy to your hand, deck, and battlefield.
102423.flavorText: Get mad at your mirror once, see Shattered Reflections forever :(

100943.name: Shell Game
100943.text: Get a random Epic, Rare, and Common card from other classes.
100943.flavorText: I thiiink… It's under all three of 'em!

100641.name: Sheriff Barrelbrim
100641.text: Battlecry: If you have 20 or less Health, open the Badlands Jail.
100641.flavorText: Is that Sheriff Barrelbrim, owner of the Badlands Barrelbuilding?

102158.name: Shimmer Shot
102158.text: Deal 1 damage. Summon a random minion of that Cost.
102158.flavorText: I hope I don't jinx the outcome.

101109.name: Showdown!
101109.text: Both players summon three 3/3 Outlaws. Give yours Rush.
101109.flavorText: An epic confrontation between the outlaws and the in-laws.

104526.name: Shroomscavate
104526.text: Give a minion Divine Shield. Excavate a treasure.
104526.flavorText: As Globb shroominated on his situation, toiling endlessly in the mushroom mines, he came to the startling realization. His boss wasn't a very fun guy.

102163.name: Sir Finley, the Intrepid
102163.text: Battlecry: If you've Excavated twice, transform all enemy minions into 1/1 Murlocs.
102163.flavorText: And exactly how does Finley turn everyone into a murloc?

100288.name: Skarr, the Catastrophe
100288.text: Battlecry: Deal damage to all enemies (improved by each turn in a row you've played an Elemental).
100288.flavorText: We're not in Karazhan anymore, Reno.

99957.name: Skeleton Crew
99957.flavorText: They don't sweat, breathe or need lit candles... what more could you ask?

101454.name: Slagmaw the Slumbering
